citeinfo.title: Geothermal Investigations in Idaho , Part 9, Potential for Direct Heat Application of Geothermal Resources

descript.abstract: This coverage shows the wells and springs in Idaho that have water temperatures that are either warm (68-85 degrees Fahrenheit), or are geothermal (> 85 degrees Fahrenheit).
descript.purpose: This layer was created in order to provide an up-to-date and accurate listing of wells and springs in Idaho that have water temperatures that reflect geothermal sources. The coverage is the result of compiling several databases that contained geothermal resources in Idaho. The initial database was produced by John Mitchell, Linda Johnson, and John Anderson, and published in the Idaho Department of Water Resources Water Information Bulletin No. 30, Part 9, "Geothermal Investigation in Idaho - Potential for Direct Heat Application of Geothermal Resources" in June, 1980. A 1:500,000 map was included with that publication. The creation of this current coverage was made possible by a grant from the U.S. Department of Energy through their GeoPowering the West Program.
descript.supplinf: Although this coverage is superior to previous databases and maps, it is not complete. As such, it will continue to undergo review and revision, and new versions will be published periodically
